Macedonians on Sunday voted in a referendum on whether to change the country's name to "Republic of North Macedonia" to resolve a decades-old dispute with Greece that has blocked applications for membership in the European Union and NATO.
Greece has a province called Macedonia and claims that the name of the northern neighbor represents a claim to its territory, and therefore has vetoed Macedonia's entry into NATO and the EU.
