“We are for NATO and the EU, but we want to enter them with our heads up, not the door for the servants,” Kavadarkov said.
“We are a poor country, but we have our pride.
If they don’t want us as Macedonia, we can turn to others like China and Russia and become part of Eurasian integration.”
Prime Minister Zaev says NATO membership will bring Macedonia, which has an unemployment rate of more than 20%, a much-needed investment.
